here(bins > 0, bins, 0)\n    return np.where(bins == np.max(bin_usage), 1, 0)\n```\n\n### Implementation 6: Least Full Bin Heuristic\nThis implementation prioritizes the least full bins.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    bin_usage = np.where(bins > 0, bins, 0)\n    return np.where(bins == np.min(bin_usage), 1, 0)\n```\n\n### Implementation 7: Middle Full Bin Heuristic\nThis implementation prioritizes bins that are neither the most nor the least full.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    bin_usage = np.where(bins > 0, bins, 0)\n    sorted_usage = np.sort(bin_usage)\n    median_usage = np.median(sorted_usage)\n    return np.abs(bin_usage - median_usage)\n```\n\n### Implementation 8: Item Size Relative to Bin Capacity Heuristic\nThis implementation prioritizes bins where the item takes up a larger proportion of the bin.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    bin_usage = bins / item\n    return np.where(bin_usage > 1, np.inf, bin_usage)\n```\n\n### Implementation 9: Diversity Heuristic\nThis implementation encourages diverse packing by sometimes preferring less filled bins.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    bin_usage = np.where(bins > 0, bins, 0)\n    diversity_score = np.std(bin_usage)\n    return np.where(np.isnan(diversity_score), 0, diversity_score)\n```\n\n### Implementation 10: Utilization Heuristic\nThis implementation prioritizes bins that have the best utilization when adding the item.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available_space = np.maximum(0, bins - item)\n    return np.where(available_space < 0, 0, available_space)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + 