ctorized, without loops or conditionals, and use a unique combination of allowed operations.\n\n### Approach\nThe task is to create 10 different functions that compute a priority score for each bin when trying to place a new item. Each function must use a unique combination of allowed mathematical operations and NumPy functions. The functions should be vectorized to ensure efficiency and avoid loops or conditionals.\n\n### Solution Code\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + bins + 1e-8)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.sin(np.pi * (item + bins)) + np.cos(item - bins) + np.tan(np.pi * item / bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.max(bins)) / (item + np.min(bins)) + np.sqrt(item + bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item + bins + 1e-8) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) / (item - bins + 1e-8) + np.exp(item * bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.sqrt(item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + bins + 1e-8)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * bins) / (item + bins) + np.exp(item - bins) * np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item + bins + 1e-8) + np.exp(item - bins) * np.cos(np.pi * item / bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(item + bins + 1e-8) * np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)\n```\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.nda