rn fit\n```\n\n### Implementation 6: Decreasing Fit Heuristic\nThis heuristic places the item in the bin with the largest remaining space that can fit it.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    fit = np.where(bins >= item, bins.max() - bins, -np.inf)\n    return fit\n```\n\n### Implementation 7: Max Decrease Heuristic\nThis heuristic places the item in the bin where it results in the largest decrease in the number of bins.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    fit = np.where(bins >= item, 1, 0)\n    fit = np.sum(fit.reshape(1, -1), axis=0)\n    return fit\n```\n\n### Implementation 8: Min Increase Heuristic\nThis heuristic places the item in the bin where it results in the smallest increase in the number of bins.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    fit = np.where(bins >= item, 1, 0)\n    fit = np.sum(fit.reshape(1, -1), axis=0)\n    return fit\n```\n\n### Implementation 9: Middle Fit Heuristic\nThis heuristic places the item in the bin with the median remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins.max() - bins\n    fit = np.where(remaining >= item, remaining, -np.inf)\n    fit = np.sort(fit)\n    fit = fit[len(fit)//2]\n    return np.full_like(bins, fit)\n```\n\n### Implementation 10: Some Other Heuristic\nThis heuristic places the item in the bin with the smallest index that can accommodate it.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    fit = np.where(bins >= item, 1, 0)\n    fit = np.argmax(fit)\n    return np.full_like(bins, fit)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.log(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.tan(np.pi * item / bins)\n', 'def priority(it