tions, as per the constraints.\n\nEach function must be a correct implementation, and all must be unique.\n</think>\n\n### Implementation 1:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(bins + 1e-8) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 2:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.log(bins + 1e-8)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 3:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.tan(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 4:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.var(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.arcsin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 5:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 6:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.log2(bins + 1e-8)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.arccos(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 7:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.power(bins, 0.5)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.arctan(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 8:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * (item - bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.log10(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 9:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * (item + bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * (np.sqrt(item) + np.sqrt(bins))) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.log(bins) + np.log(item)) * np.exp(it